properties.name: NRMA Port Campbell Holiday Park
properties.description:
The Great Ocean Road is calling
It’s one of Australia’s most iconic drives, where a dramatic limestone coastline is dotted with sleepy seaside towns. Your Great Ocean Road getaway awaits, and NRMA Port Campbell Holiday Park is the perfect base for adventure.

Tucked in a quiet corner beside the beach and Port Campbell Creek, the scene is set for total relaxation. Think sunsets over reedy wetlands teeming with life. Comfy accommodation beside the creek or a spacious campsite metres from the sand. A friendly coastal village within walking distance, where local flavours are served fresh. Crystal clear waters to cool off in, and a jetty over the ocean to dangle a line. This will be a holiday to remember in a place made for making memories.

properties.name: NRMA Phillip Island Beachfront Holiday Park
properties.description:
An unforgettable island getaway starts here
For a relaxing island getaway where the coastal villages are as charming as the little penguins that march up the beach of an evening, head to NRMA Phillip Island Beachfront Holiday Park.

Just a stone’s throw from Melbourne but a world away, everything you need for a relaxing and fun trip is right here. Whether you choose a comfortable cabin or a spacious caravan or campsite, you’ll be metres from the beach – and your pet is welcome, too. Best of all, the shops and restaurants of Cowes are within walking distance. So go on, order another glass of wine with dinner. You’re on holiday, after all.

And when it’s time to explore the natural beauty of Phillip Island, our famously friendly hosts are on-site to help plan your adventure.

properties.name: NRMA Halls Gap Holiday Park
properties.description:
The mountains are calling
With home in the rear-view mirror, you’ll be toasting marshmallows, spotting constellations and planning tomorrow’s Grampians adventure in no time. NRMA Halls Gap Holiday Park welcomes you for a memorable getaway in the mountains.

Whether your style is a cabin or camping, you’ll enjoy a welcoming, friendly atmosphere with endless possibilities to explore and discover our land. With rock-climbing, abseiling, and hiking on the cards, this will be an adventure to remember.

Back at camp, the kids can test their survival skills and more with our Bear Grylls Survival Academy, while you relax in the heated pool or sauna. At Halls Gap Holiday Park, everything you need to make your trip comfortable, fun and extra special is right here.

properties.name: Tasman Holiday Parks - Geelong
properties.description:
Set amongst beautiful gum trees near the banks of the Barwon River, our park is perfectly situated for a weekend break or family holiday.

Just over an hour from Melbourne, and minutes from the heart of Geelong, it’s a great base to explore the Surf Coast and Bellarine Peninsula, and the cosmopolitan charms of Victoria’s second biggest city.

Spend your days surfing, swimming, fishing, walking and exploring and return to the park to chill by the pool, wind down in the games room, or just relax with a glass of wine or cuppa.

Meals are easy with a camp kitchens, free BBQs and sheltered outdoor dining areas. Picnic on the riverbank or take a short drive to the Geelong waterfront for a choice of great restaurants, bars and cafes.

properties.name: Surfside Holiday Park
properties.description: Surfside Holiday Park is the ideal location for you to stay. Positioned on Warrnambool’s beautiful foreshore with easy access to our wonderful beach via the boardwalk, located just a short stroll from your camp site.

properties.name: NRMA Bairnsdale Riverside Holiday Park
properties.description:
Total riverside relaxation? You’ve made it.
With home in the rear-view mirror, you’ll be relaxing riverside, fishing from our private jetty and planning tomorrow’s East Gippsland adventure in no time. NRMA Bairnsdale Riverside Holiday Park welcomes you for a restful escape on the Mitchell River.

Whether your style is a cabin or a spacious caravan site amongst our leafy grounds, you’ll enjoy a laid back, friendly atmosphere with endless possibilities to explore and discover our land. With fishing, boating, and four-wheel driving on the cards, there’s as much or as little to do as you like.

Back at camp, relax beside our sparkling pool, hang out in the shade beside the river and enjoy being an easy stroll from the restaurants and shops of Bairnsdale.

properties.name: Apex RiverBeach Holiday Park
properties.description: A quiet, tranquil setting just 5 minutes from the heart of Mildura. Set on 25 acres and surrounded by a sandy beach on the Murray River and the state forest. An ideal location for fishing, swimming, bird watching, or bush walking. Also a great base for exploring the local region for golf, wineries, National Parks, historic features or day trips to nearby Wentworth and South Australia’s Riverland. We have pet friendly cabins and a hydrobath to keep your pooch clean and happy.

properties.name: Forrest Holiday Park
properties.description:
Welcome to the Forrest Holiday Park, located in the beautiful township of Forrest in the Otway Ranges. Forrest is 2 hours drive from Melbourne and in close proximity to the spectacular Great Ocean Road.
Forrest Holiday Park provides a range of facilities and amenities to help make your stay more comfortable including:
- Two Tennis Courts
- Kids Play Area
- Brand New Camp Kitchen
- Amenities Block
- Mountain Views
- Grassed Areas

Enjoy a hit of tennis while the kids play in the nearby playground and skate area or take to the endless kilometers of pristine mountain biking trails located on our doorstep. For those looking for a more relaxing day, paddle out on the nearby Lake Elizabeth and go platypus spotting.  

With a brand new camp kitchen, campsites, standard and family glamping tents and ensuite cabins, the park is perfect for your next holiday and is set on approximately 15 acres with a lovely panoramic view taking in undulating landscape and bush surrounds.

properties.name: Rich River Tourist Park
properties.description: Our park is compact and very quiet at night due to being away from the main highway. A short walk will have you on the banks of the mighty Murray River and the boat ramp and sandy beach is a mere 350 metres from the park gate. The town centre and historic port of Echuca is a short distance away with all the shops, facilities, pubs, clubs and eateries needed to enjoy your stay.

properties.name: A-Line Holiday Park
properties.description: A-Line Holiday Park Bendigo offer a selection of accommodation options in Bendigo. We strive to provide excellent and clean comfortable facilities to make your stay as enjoyable and relaxing as possible. we offer great value personal touches as well as so much more as you will see and experience when you visit us.

properties.name: NRMA Portland Bay Holiday Park
properties.description:
A holiday on the coast to remember
Welcome to Portland Bay, where you’ll discover so much more than just a relaxed beachside holiday. World Heritage-listed Indigenous sites that tell of 30,000 years of permanent inhabitation and fish trapping. Streets dotted with heritage buildings steeped in European history, where inspiring foodie outlets, galleries and shops now reside. A wild and wonderful coastline home to fur seals and visited by thousands of whales. Iconic hiking trails and world-class game fishing.

Then, after an action-packed day, retreat to your comfortable cabin or spacious caravan site on a quiet clifftop overlooking the bay. Take a moment to yourself while the kids are entertained with our school holiday activities, or strike up a chat with our friendly team about how best to take on tomorrow’s adventures.

properties.name: Rochester Riverside Holiday Park
properties.description: Rochester Riverside Holiday Park is nestled along the banks of the beautiful Campaspe River with only a 2 minute walk into the centre of town where you can shop, wine and dine at your leisure. Drop a line, relax or visit the regions many attractions. We cater for campers, caravans and motorhomes of all sizes with powered sites, camping sites and ensuite sites.

properties.name: NRMA Mildura Riverside Holiday Park
properties.description:
A riverside retreat that’s full of surprises
Welcome to a Murray River getaway without the hard work. Fresh country air to breathe in a bushland setting that feels remote but is close to town. Fun family activities for a holiday they’ll remember forever (did somebody say waterslides?). A modern cabin or a pet-friendly caravan site for restful nights and relaxing days beside the river. Inspiring foodie outlets and farm experiences to discover in a region known as Australia’s food bowl.

At NRMA Mildura Riverside Holiday Park, you’ll feel right at home but without any of the housework (that’s our job). We’ve thought of everything to make your trip relaxing, easy and extra special so you can focus on what really matters: spending time together in a place made for making memories.

properties.name: NRMA Eastern Beach Holiday Park
properties.description:
A watery wonderland awaits
Fishos and beach-lovers assemble, this will be a holiday to remember. NRMA Eastern Beach Holiday Park is in the heart of the Gippsland Lakes at Lakes Entrance. Our waterfront location and fun facilities set the scene for an unforgettable adventure.

From the moment you arrive you’ll feel right at home. The kids will make a bee line for our heated swimming pool, bouncing pillow and playground, while our school holiday activities keep them entertained (and you, relaxed). There’s much fun and frivolity to be had at our hosted events, including live music nights and footy finals on the big screen.

At Eastern Beach Holiday Park, a warm welcome is in our nature.

properties.name: Ingenia Holidays Inverloch
properties.description:
Welcome to Ingenia Holidays Inverloch. You’ll find it located on Anderson Inlet, close to nearby natural attractions of Phillip Island and Wilson’s Promontory, a short 90 minutes’ drive from Melbourne’s CBD.  

Accommodation comes in all shapes and sizes from caravan and camping to cabins and luxury villas. Spend your days exploring the seaside village of Inverloch, which is nestled at the mouth of Anderson Inlet, a protected bay where the Tarwin River enters the Bass Strait.

If the Victorian weather plays nice for your visit, swim at the region’s turquoise beaches or enjoy a picnic along its foreshore.

For those partial to a scenic drive, don’t miss the 12-kilometre scenic Bunurong Coastal Drive from Inverloch to Cape Paterson, hugging the Bunurong Marine Park.

Said to be a ‘mini version of the Great Ocean Road’, you’re in for a road trip pretty enough to land itself in a car commercial – perfect to keep up your sleeve for a free family day out during your stay.

properties.name: The Paddock at Ulupna
properties.description: The Paddock at Ulupna! Located just three hours north of Melbourne on 180 acres of beautiful Australian bushland, our property offers a picturesque escape.

properties.name: NRMA Ballarat Holiday Park
properties.description:
Discover the riches of yesterday while enjoying modern comforts at NRMA Ballarat Holiday Park. Situated just a stone’s throw from Melbourne, there’s much to love here, starting with our proximity to the award-winning Sovereign Hill living museum.

The whole family will delight at meeting the colourful characters of the gold rush as they go about their lives in this preserved historic village.

properties.name: Tawonga Tourist Park
properties.description:
Welcome to Tawonga Tourist Park, where adventure meets relaxation in the heart of Victoria's stunning High Country. We're excited to announce that we're officially open after extensive refurbishment and a range of exciting new additions.

Our brand new reception area is waiting to welcome you, along with a new café and retail area where you can relax and unwind after a day of exploring. And speaking of exploring, our newly refurbished cabins are looking absolutely gorgeous and are the perfect base for your next adventure.

We've also added a nature play playground, perfect for families looking to immerse themselves in the great outdoors. And if that wasn't enough, we've undergone extensive underground infrastructure works to ensure that your stay is as comfortable and convenient as possible.

Tawonga Tourist Park is nestled in a beautiful valley surrounded by the unique Bogong National Park and magnificent Bogong high plains. With easy access from Albury/Wodonga, Wangaratta and surrounding historic townships, our park is the perfect destination for your next holiday.

Whether you're interested in fishing, skiing, hiking, swimming or simply relaxing by the camp fire, we've got you covered. Our range of facilities, including newly refurbished cabins, amenities blocks, kiosk and cafe, BBQ area, and camp kitchen, are designed to make your stay as enjoyable as possible.

And if you're looking for something a little extra special, keep an eye out for our upcoming glamping facilities, coming soon!

We can't wait to see you at Tawonga Tourist Park!

properties.name: Ingenia Holidays Phillip Island
properties.description:
Whether you’re visiting to catch a glimpse of the largest Little Penguin colony in the world or escaping for a family holiday along Victoria’s southern coastline, check into Ingenia Holidays Phillip Island.

Set in a cul-de-sac, Ingenia Holidays Phillip Island provides the ultimate beachfront location paired with a natural bush setting.

Put animal encounters on your to-list during your stay and book the world-famous Penguin Parade, visit the Koala Conservation Centre or stop by The Nobbies, to see local fur seals in their natural habitat.

properties.name: NRMA Echuca Holiday Park
properties.description:
A home among the river gum trees
Welcome to NRMA Echuca Holiday Park, where your home away from home is set on the banks of the Murray River. Perfect for the young and the young at heart alike, kids will have a ball playing for hours at the heated swimming pool and riding their bikes around our leafy grounds. Meanwhile, our boat ramp provides direct access to the river, so you might just land a Murray cod or finally try wakeboarding.

But it wouldn’t be a trip to Echuca without a cruise on a historic paddle steamer. You can reach the port within walking distance, along with riverside dining options.

From fishing at daybreak until happy hour at camp, this will be a getaway to remember in a place made for adventure.

properties.name: Holiday Lifestyle Henty Bay Portland
properties.description:
Holiday Lifestyle Henty Bay Portland is picturesque, relaxing and peaceful; perfect for your next break. All styles of accommodation are available, including camping, cabins, group accommodation, luxury villas, and ensuite and powered sites.

Giant jumping pillow, wide open spaces, and a games room with entertain the kids!

properties.name: Ingenia Holidays Cape Paterson
properties.description:
We say Great Breaks. Great Places. And at Ingenia Holidays Cape Paterson, we mean it with six local beaches, pristine waters, a rock pool to explore and Bass Coast vistas. Located in Cape Paterson, a small seaside village in South Gippsland, 90 minutes’ drive from Melbourne, this holiday park is the perfect basecamp for fishing, surfing, swimming or beach walks.

Spend your days relaxing at one of the secluded beaches, exploring the nearby town of Wonthaggi, or sipping your way through local South Gippsland wineries less than 30 minutes’ drive from the holiday park.

properties.name: Ingenia Holidays Torquay
properties.description:
Searching for a surfing escape in Victoria? Head to Ingenia Holidays Torquay to soak up the beachside atmosphere at one of Victoria’s best-known surfing locations.

Located less than one kilometre from the Torquay Foreshore, Torquay Beach and The Esplanade, this is one destination best explored on foot, with local shops, cafes and restaurants on the holiday park’s doorstep.

While the coastline might be the main attraction with over 20 beaches and coves to explore in the Torquay region, the holiday park gives you plenty of excuses not to leave with a solar-heated swimming pool, heated spa and landscaped gardens. With mini-golf, tennis courts, cricket nets, modern playground and games room – there are plenty of activities to keep the kids entertained when they’re not splashing about.

Choose from a studio to a three-bedroom unit or book a powered site to camp or set up the caravan – including a selection of sites with synthetic turf.

properties.name: Halls Gap Lakeside Tourist Park
properties.description: Breathtaking views of the mountains, abundance of Australian Wildlife, spacious powered campsites, excellent facilities, a wide variety of cabin accommodation and a very warm welcome! The perfect base to explore the Grampians. Have a dip in our woodfire heated outdoor pool and enjoy a campfire at night. No matter if you live nearby or come from afar, you will absolutely love the fact you found this place!

properties.name: Geelong Surfcoast Highway Holiday Park
properties.description: Geelong Surfcoast Highway Holiday Park is located only minutes from the start of the Great Ocean Road, the Geelong CBD and the world renowned beaches of Torquay. The park offers a choice of motel units, deluxe cabins and ensuite powered sites. Facilities include a shaded baby pool, swimming pool and spa. There is a camp kitchen, BBQ area along with a playground, games and TV room. We also have pet friendly cabins.

properties.name: Creswick Holiday Park
properties.description:
Welcome to Creswick Holiday Park
Creswick is a historic former gold-mining town, located between Ballarat and Daylesford, approximately a 2 hour drive from Melbourne.

With standard and family cabins, couples and family glamping tents and a range of campsites, Creswick Holiday Park provides a range of facilities and amenities to help make your stay more comfortable. Please find the list of amenities available to all guests: 
- Coin operated laundry machines 
- Amenities block with toilets and hot showers 
- Children’s playground 
- Communal camp kitchen
- Dump Point
- Shaded areas 
- We are also pet friendly

Creswick offers a number of natural attractions and outdoor activities for visitors, set within an attractive forested area. Enjoy bushwalking and scenic drives through the extensive Creswick Regional Park. Visit Calambeen Park which was the town's Chinese camp in the goldmining days and now features lakes which are suitable for fishing or swimming. Park Lake Botanical Reserve, located on the Midland Highway, is a 15 hectare park which was established in 1860 and features a lake, rotunda, established trees and recreational facilities.

properties.name: Tasman Holiday Parks - South Bright
properties.description:
Picture-perfect in every season, Bright is a small and vibrant resort town in the heart of Victoria's glorious Alpine country.

Just over three hours drive from Melbourne, and seven hours from Sydney, our premium South Bright holiday park offers hours of family fun.

Relax in one of our pools, drink in the scenic beauty of the mountains. Don’t worry about the kids! They can swim, bounce, play, or kick back with games and TV.

Some of Victoria’s best seasonal skiing lies just beyond the caravan park. Bright is also brimming with outdoor pursuits, bustling markets, boutique stores, quality wines and the tastiest food.

If you love the great outdoors, you've come to the right place! Try cycling, hiking, paragliding, skiing (in season), rock climbing, caving and mountain biking. We have a huge range of accommodation options, so you’re sure to find something to suit. From powered sites to standard cabins, from deluxe units to a four-bedroom home, there’s something for everyone!

properties.name: NRMA Bright Holiday Park
properties.description:
Welcome to a High Country getaway without the hard work. Fresh mountain air to breathe and a thriving village within walking distance. A modern villa or a shaded campsite for restful nights and relaxing days beside a clear, flowing creek. Fun family activities for a holiday they’ll remember forever. A natural adventure playground waiting to be discovered, with bucketloads of fun on offer in every season.

At NRMA Bright Holiday Park, you’ll feel right at home but without any of the housework (that’s our job). We’ve thought of everything to make your trip relaxing, easy and extra special so you can focus on what really matters: spending time together in a place made for making memories.

properties.name: Ingenia Holidays Queenscliff Beacon
properties.description:
Looking for a touch of luxe during your next family getaway? Set your sights on Ingenia Holidays Queenscliff Beacon for a dose of relaxation and rejuvenation on the Bellarine Peninsula.

In less than 90 minutes’ drive from Melbourne CBD, you can be checking into a luxury one, two or three-bedroom villa, modern apartment or self-contained cabin. If you prefer to BYO your accommodation,  Ingenia Holidays Queenscliff Beacon also offers caravan and camping sites with artificial turf or natural grass sites, bathroom amenities, a camp kitchen and wireless internet.

properties.name: NRMA Warrnambool Riverside Holiday Park
properties.description:
Your coastal riverside retreat awaits.

In a quiet rural setting on the banks of the Hopkins River you’ll find NRMA Warrnambool Riverside Holiday Park, close to town but far from the crowds.

Everything you need for a relaxing and easy coastal getaway is right here – including year-round fun for the kids. They’ll delight in our waterslide, playground and mini golf course, and our school holiday activities will keep them busy.

That’ll free you up to relax at our indoor or outdoor pool or take a rod down to the river to cast a line from the jetty. You might just return with an estuary perch to cook up at our communal barbecue area. And when it comes to exploring our coastal surroundings, our friendly team is on-site to help plan your adventure.

properties.name: Wilsons Promontory Day Tour
properties.description:
Explore the pristine wilderness of "The Prom," the first National Park established in Australia all the way back in 1898, and still one of Victoria's most beloved natural attractions. As you wander along its well-preserved walking tracks, you'll be inspired and intrigued by the panoramic views, pristine white beaches, coastal forests, and cool climate rainforests that abound. 

Don't miss the chance to enjoy fabulous coastal views on the walk from "Squeaky" Beach to Tidal River, and keep your eyes peeled for the abundant native wildlife that calls this park home, from kangaroos and emus to wombats and more. Take some time to relax at Tidal River and learn more about this spectacular southernmost region of Victoria. 

For those who love the outdoors, this day is filled with adventure; whether you're awestruck by the Summit views from Mt Bishop, witnessing the sheer power of the ocean, or feeling the sand squeak beneath your feet as you stroll along one of Australia's most famous beaches, "Squeaky Beach", get ready for an unforgettable experience in the heart of nature.

properties.name: Dolphin and Seal Swim Tour - Queenscliff
properties.description:
Melbourne Dolphin Swim Day Tour | Experience OzHow many places in the world can you swim with wild dolphins AND seals? Few, but Victoria's Queenscliff is one of them. People travel from all over the world to experience what we have on our very doorstep. 

Whether a planned trip, a surprise or even a gift voucher - its the ultimate way to explore Port Phillip Bay on this dolphin and seal swim tour. Tours last for 3.5 hours and give guests a great understanding and experience of the area's local wildlife. The cruise boat is well equipped and tours are suitable for all ages and fitness levels

properties.name: Mornington Peninsula Sightseeing Cruise
properties.description:
Experience all the highlights of the Mornington Peninsula adored by locals on this full day sightseeing tour with a 2 hour sail around the bay and a delicious hamper for lunch. 

Victoria's spectacular coastline, natural wonders and farmlands are on full display with stops at London Bridge- a natural rock formation to behold, down a tasty beer paddle at St Andrews Beach Brewery, admire stunning 360 degree views from Murrays Lookout at Arthurs Seat and go for a relaxing lunchtime sail across the bay. T

o cap it all off, a visit to the colourful Peninsula Bathing Boxes and a stroll on the beach make for a great photo opportunity and is the perfect way to end a spectacular day out in the Mornington Peninsula.

**Highlights** 

- Spend the day gazing upon the picturesque coastline
- Sail the bay whilst enjoying a delicious hamper lunch
- Enjoy a beer paddle tasting at St. Andrews Brewery
- Ride the Arthurs Seat Eagle for breathtaking views
- See the iconic Peninsula Bathing boxes
- See the London Bridge set upon Portsea Beach

properties.name: Puffing Billy Lakeside to Gembrook Return Tickets
properties.description:
All aboard the Puffing Billy for a relaxing journey through the Dandenong Ranges from Lakeside to Gembrook on the heritage steam train. 

Experience a piece of Victorian history as you travel along the original mountain track taking the sights. The experience is great for families and railway enthusiasts alike who will be taken from the Wright Forest to the rich farmlands of Gembrook.

Highlights: 

- Authentic heritage steam train experience, established in 1900
- Travel in heritage open sided carriages
- Travel over four historic timber trestle bridges
- Engage with knowledgable volunteers
- Experience a part of Victorian history
- Marvel at the iconic Dandenong ranges

properties.name: Puffing Billy Belgrave to Lakeside Return Tickets
properties.description:
Explore the Dandenong Ranges on the historic Puffing Billy steam railway from Belgrave to Lakeside. Share the joy as you pass lush fern gullies deep in the rainforest on the heritage open carriage railway. The Puffing Billy is a piece of Victorian history to share with the family and take in the sights with a stop at Lakeside. 

**Highlights** 

- Authentic heritage steam train experience, established in 1900 
- Travel in heritage open sided carriages 
- Travel over four historic timber trestle bridges 
- Engage with knowledgable volunteers 
- Experience a part of Victorian history 
- Marvel at the iconic Dandenong ranges

properties.name: Moonlit Sanctuary
properties.description:
Grab your tickets to this charming wildlife conservation park on the Mornington Peninsula - the Moonlit Sanctuary - online here and see all the rare Aussie animals that make the centre great! 

Also known as Pearcedale Conservation Park, the Moonlit Sanctuary lets you cuddle up to a koala, meet kangaroos, dingoes, wombats and colourful birds all in the name of eco-tourism. 

Highlights:

- Cuddle a koala
- Feed kangaroos
- Just 1 hour outside Melbourne
- See over 60 species of Aussie animals
- Perfect for families
- Great for all ages

properties.name: Legoland Discovery Centre
properties.description:
Take the kids to the amazing LEGOLAND attraction in the Chadstone shopping centre with the LEGOLAND Discovery Centre Single Entry Tickets. 

Step into the world of LEGOLAND where the kids can explore the exciting LEGO-themed rides, the replicas of local and global landmarks made out of millions of LEGO bricks in MINILAND, the 5 LEGO build and play areas, as well as a 4D cinema. 

**Highlights** - Buy online and save - 2 LEGO rides - 10 LEGO build & play zones - 4D cinema... and much more! - LEGO factory tour - Skip the queues with express mobile ticket entry

properties.name: Ballarat Wildlife Park
properties.description:
Visit the popular, family-run Ballarat Wildlife Park in Victoria and get up close with a wide variety of native Aussie and exotic animals. 

There are few friendlier or more personal wildlife attractions in Australia than this facility where you can come face-to-face with a wide assortment of creatures including kangaroos, koalas, wombats, crocodiles and more all located in pleasant, green surroundings.

**Highlights**  

-   Personal animal encounters available
-   See a variety of exotic animals, like the Sumatran Tigers!
-   Less than 10 min drive from main Ballarat
-   Animal presentations throughout the day
-   New digital self-guided tour
-   Licensed Cafe on site - Or BYO Picnic

properties.name: Port Phillip Bay Wildlife Sightseeing Tour
properties.description:
Watch in wonder and amazement as pods of dolphins and seals swim right alongside the vessel on this Queenscliff dolphin sightseeing cruise. Over the course of 90 minutes, you'll get up close and personal with a myriad of curious and playful marine creatures including Australian Fur Seals playing, pods of dolphins gleefully darting in and out of the water and Humpback Whales making their annual winter migration.

The vessel is equipped with a rooftop viewing platform to enjoy uninterrupted sightseeing of the wildlife.

Highlights: 

- Rooftop viewing platform
- Available October to May
- Port Phillip Bay Marine Park
- Snacks and light refreshments
- Spot pods of Burrunan dolphins
- Watch playful Australian fur seals

properties.name: Tandem Skydive over the 12 Apostles - 10000ft
properties.description:
Take the ultimate leap of faith on an extraordinary tandem skydive from 10,000ft over the 12 Apostles and Great Ocean Road in Victoria. This mind blowing experience is one for the thrill seekers with an invigorating freefall of up to 60 seconds offering unique aerial views only skydivers are treated to.

**Highlights**  

-   Tandem skydive from up to 10,000 feet over the 12 Apostles
-   Experience the indescribable feeling of freefall
-   Uninterrupted views of Loch Arch Gorge and the 12 Apostles

-   Picturesque 5-7 minute scenic flight under the parachute canopy
-   Unbeatable adrenaline rush with a skydive instructor
-   Witness one of Australia's greatest natural wonders from a unique perspective

properties.name: Otways Wildlife Sanctuary
properties.description:
Watch the sunset dip below the horizon on the Great Ocean Road as friendly nocturnal creatures come out to play on this exclusive after hours tour of the Wildlife Wonders animal sanctuary in Apollo Bay. Taking place at dusk, join conservationist guides for a mezze plate and a glass of wine or beer before embarking on a gentle evening walk in the Otways.

Highlights: 

- Guided tour of the amazing Wildlife Wonders sanctuary at dusk
- Spot stunning wildlife and enjoy plenty of photography opportunities
- Includes mezze platter of local produce and a glass of wine or beer before your tour
- 90-minute guided tour with a conservationist guide
- Witness the magic of the night as nocturnal animals of Wildlife Wonders come out to play
- Unique after hours experience with conservationist guides on a small, private group tour

properties.name: Cactus Country
properties.description:
Experience something out of this world. Cactus Country (as seen on Better Homes & Gardens) is an Australian desert landscape like no other. Drawing visitors from around the globe to explore the gardens and marvel at the blooms, shapes and sizes of these spiky sensations. Get ready to discover more than 4,000 species of cacti and succulents.

Sandy walking trails weave their way through the 12 acres of garden making for an unforgettable trip. There are eight paths to explore and plenty to see and do for all ages, even the four-legged variety.

When it comes time to refuel the mind, body and soul, Cactus Country offers a range of refreshments including cactus cake, cactus ice cream, honey collected from on site bee hives and even cactus cider! The onsite nursery has a huge range of varieties for purchase so you can start your own cactus garden at home.

Pack your walking shoes and camera and uncover this little piece of Mexico right here in Strathmerton.

properties.name: Chocoholic Tours
properties.description:
Discover and learn about Melbourne's lanes and arcades while eating Chocolate. Chocolate Tastings include Belgium, Swiss, Australian and French style Chocolate.

Chocoholic Tours has been sharing chocolate since 1995. Discover and learn about Melbourne's lanes and arcades while indulging in Belgium, Swiss, French and Australian style chocolates. We will take you on a world class walking tour experience to some of the best Chocolate boutiques Melbourne has to offer.

properties.name: Phillip Island Penguin Parade
properties.description:
Watch Little Penguins dash across the sand at sunset with a visit to the Penguin Parade. The explore the boardwalks after dark to see, smell and hear Little Penguins in the colony returning home to their burrows, greeting neighbours and their chicks. 

While you're here, make sure you keep an eye out for other local residents including Swamp Wallabies, Eastern Barred Bandicoots, Cape Barren Geese and Short-tailed Shearwaters.

Highlights:

- Phillip Island Penguin Parade
- Only 90 minutes from Melbourne
- Protect nature for wildlife with every visit
- Watch penguins waddle home at sunset
- Largest Little Penguin colony in the world
- Wander the boardwalks in the colony after dark

properties.name: Great Ocean Road Tandem Skydive
properties.description:
See the Great Ocean Road from a different perspective on this tandem skydive. This skydiving experience is perfect for the thrill seekers looking for the ultimate adrenaline rush. 

The skydive experience begins with a personalised safety briefing and brief scenic flight over the Great Ocean Road. Once you reach elevations of up to 15,000 ft, the plane door opens and you will take the plunge with your tandem skydive instructor. 

Experience an unforgettable 60 second free fall at speeds up to 220km/hr. 

Once the canopy opens, soak in the impressive aerial views of the Great Ocean Road on your flight back down to base. This is one of the most picturesque places in Australia to skydive.

properties.name: SEA LIFE Melbourne Aquarium
properties.description:
SEA LIFE Melbourne Aquarium is one of Melbourne’s top attractions for families. Discover a dazzling display of marine life for yourself with these great value tickets to the must-see aquarium. Located in the heart of Melbourne CBD on the banks of the Yarra River, SEA LIFE Melbourne Aquarium is home to thousands of sea critters spread across 12 different zones. See Antarctic Penguins slip and slide in their cosy exhibit and don’t miss out on the brand new ‘Ocean Invaders’ exhibit that will take you inside the mysterious world of jellyfish.

It’s an attraction where fun and learning go hand in hand with daily shark and ray feedings and animal presentations taking place. Extra activities such as the 4D cinema show, the hands-on touch pools and kids activities make it a great day out for all ages. In total, there are over 10,000 animals on display at SEA LIFE Melbourne Aquarium making it a must-visit attraction in Melbourne - so be sure to grab your tickets online here today.

properties.name: Sovereign Hill Gold Rush Living Museum
properties.description:
Sovereign Hill is a living museum presenting the story of Ballarat as a goldrush boomtown. Gold was discovered here in 1851, triggering the greatest alluvial gold rush the world has ever known. The sleepy pastoral settlement of Ballarat grew rapidly into a fine provincial city built on the wealth derived from its gold.
Covering 15 hectares of a former gold mining site, Sovereign Hill's Outdoor Museum brings the gold rush to life through a living township with over 18 scheduled activities happening throughout the day, you can find yourself panning for real gold, witness musket firing, see boiled lollies, wheels, and candles being made all before your very eyes.

The Outdoor Museum enjoys international renown as a living museum featuring rare trades, working machinery, exhibits, and costumed interpreters.

Daily Activities include: 

- The Diggings Tour
- The Red Hill Mine Tou
- Gold panning
- Musket Firing
- Wheelwrighting and more!

properties.name: Phillip Island Nature Parks Multi Park Pass
properties.description:
Have fun while supporting conservation with a Phillip Island Nature Parks 4 Park Pass. Watch Little Penguins waddle home from the ocean at the Penguin Parade. Spy koalas in their natural bushland environment at Koala Conservation Reserve along treetop boardwalks. Explore climate resilience, conservation, and the secrets of life in Antarctica at the interactive Antarctic Journey. Finally, wander the tranquil gardens, partake in farming activities, and explore early European farming at Churchill Island.

Penguins Plus provides a more intimate experience with a smaller capacity and located right beside our main penguin highway from the ocean. General Viewing has excellent views of the Little Penguins waddling up the beach and into the colony.

Phillip Island Nature Parks' is visitor-funded and its team care for more than 1805 hectares of wild spaces on Phillip Island. Phillip Island is a 90-minute drive from Melbourne and the 4 Parks Pass provides a unique educational experience for everyone to enjoy - so grab yours online today!

Highlights:

- See Koalas up close at the Koala Conservation Reserve
- Experience the natural wonder of the Penguin Parade
- Explore the historical grounds of Churchill Island
- Combine attractions and SAVE!
- See more and save with a 4 Park Pass
- Embark on a virtual Antarctic Journey at the Nobbies Centre

properties.name: Otway Fly Treetop Adventures
properties.description:
The ultimate nature-based attraction in the lush hinterland of Victoria, the Otway Fly Treetop Walk will let you stroll along the highest and longest walk of its kind in the world, located 2.5 hours from Melbourne and 1.5 hours from Geelong. 

Walk through verdant rainforests 30 metres above the forest floor surrounded by nature that grants great views of all the surrounds and culminates in the Spiral Tower at the end of the walkway that provides an awesome vantage point to gaze out into the views in the distance.

**Highlights** 
- Buy online and save 
- Up to 47m above the forest floor 
- Amazing Victorian scenery 
- 1.9km Interpretive Walk 
- World's highest walk of its kind 
- Prehistoric path for the kids

**highlights:**

properties.name: BIG4 Kerang Riverfront Holiday Park

properties.name: BIG4 Borderland Wodonga Holiday Park

properties.name: BIG4 Yarra Valley Park Lane Holiday Park

properties.name: BIG4 Melbourne Holiday Park

properties.name: Tasman Holiday Parks - Warrnambool Figtree

properties.name: Aboriginal Heritage Walk Melbourne Gardens
properties.description:
The Melbourne Royal Botanic Gardens are a significant cultural site for the local Kulin Nation, an alliance of five Indigenous Australian Nations in south central Victoria, Australia. 

The Kulin Nation extends around Port Phillip and Western Port, into the Great Dividing Range, the Loddon and Goulburn River valleys. Experience the culture and customs of the Kulin Nation as you follow an Aboriginal guide on a 90 minute walking tour. 

Learn about the rich history, thriving culture and connection.

properties.name: Gardens Port Fairy Caravan Park
properties.description:
Nestled beside the picturesque Botanic Gardens on the banks of the Moyne River and just a stone’s throw from the ever-popular East Beach, a tranquil break is awaiting you at the Gardens Caravan Park.

Ideal for the whole family with grassy open spaces surrounded by the iconic Norfolk pine trees, this caravan park is perfectly located to ensure that the whole family enjoys the variety of attractions that Port Fairy offers its guests.

Smell the sea air and enjoy the natural open spaces from the deck of a self-contained cabin, or choose one of the spacious, grassed camping sites for the duration of your stay.

Just 600 metres from the Port Fairy town centre, this dog-friendly caravan park is ideally situated for all of your holiday activities. Gather your group large or small, and relax and recharge in these idyllic surroundings.

properties.name: Lake Boga Caravan Park
properties.description:
We’re located only minutes from historical Swan Hill, a small town founded in the early 1850s as the Murray regions major inland trading port. There is plenty of history to enjoy on your visit, but with Lake Boga right at your doorstep, we can’t guarantee you’ll make it out of our Swan Hill holiday park that often!

We’re the closest large body of water to Swan Hill, so our guests relish staying on a beautiful lake within easy proximity to Swan Hill and its retail shops and services.

Camping in Lake Boga is a water sports fan’s paradise. The lake is over 9 square kilometres, providing ample space for you to make memories with your family and friends on this water lover’s playground.

properties.name: Koroit Tower Hill Caravan Park
properties.description:
Located in the historic Irish township of Koroit you’ll be sure to experience Irish hospitality at its most charming. The Koroit-Tower Hill Caravan Park is only a five-minute walk to the Koroit town centre and is located at the beautiful and historic Botanic Gardens.

The park is ideally placed right on the doorstep of the Tower Hill State Game Reserve, an inactive volcano where you can enjoy a picnic or walk around the crater to see its wildlife or to study its geology and rich indigenous cultural history. The emus tend to become very friendly when there is food around, so be sure to guard your sandwiches!

With public transport to and from Warrnambool and Port Fairy, Koroit is nestled between rolling green pastures and is the ideal place to stay when experiencing all that the region has to offer.

properties.name: Yambuk Lake Caravan Park
properties.description:
Experience Mother Nature at her finest…

Yambuk is a relaxed rural area just a short drive from the historic township of Port Fairy. This peaceful park in an idyllic location has all that you require for a relaxing stay whilst reconnecting with nature. Nestled beside the tranquil Yambuk Lake, you can pitch your tent or pull up your caravan and sit back and enjoy the serenity. The park is a prime location for families, with excellent fishing available in the lake or nearby surf beaches.

When visiting Yambuk, no stay is complete without experiencing one of the Great South region’s largest slides. Climb to the top of the famous Yambuk slide and zoom down to the bottom – this is fun for the whole family.

Yambuk also boasts a general store and a pub to complete your stay. Other activities include walking, sightseeing and day trips to several regional tourist attractions, including Port Fairy, Budj Bim indigenous history and the Codrington Wind Farm.

properties.name: Discovery Parks - Melbourne
properties.description:
There’s nothing quite like Melbourne - an unbeatable mix of sport, food, fashion, culture and great coffee! 

There’s no need to stay in the city when Discovery Parks - Melbourne (formerly Ashley Gardens Holiday Village) is just 30 minutes from the CBD. 

You’ll entertain the whole family – the Melbourne Star, Aquarium, cafe culture, shopping or Queen Victoria Markets. 

The MCG and Etihad Stadium are close by or wander through iconic St Kilda and treat the kids at Luna Park.

properties.name: Dartmouth Pub
properties.description:
At the foothills of the North East Victorian Alps, Dartmouth Pub is a welcoming haven for locals and visitors alike. Established as a hub for the community, the pub offers a warm atmosphere, delicious food, and a place to unwind after a day exploring the Mitta Valley.

Step inside and be greeted by friendly staff and a menu featuring classic pub fare with a focus on fresh, local produce. Whether you're a keen angler seeking post-fishing refreshments, a family looking for a relaxed dining experience, or a group planning a special event, the Dartmouth Pub caters to all.

We also have free unpowered camping sites with the most amazing hot showers, grass picnic and sheltered BBQ areas, coin operated laundry and dump point.

For those seeking adventure, the pub is conveniently located close to various outdoor activities. Explore the surrounding trails, or simply relax and take in the beauty of the Mitta Valley.

Looking for a pub with a rich history, delicious food, and a welcoming atmosphere? Look no further than the Dartmouth Pub.

properties.name: Tae Rak Guided Cultural Walk
properties.description:
Your Gunditjmara cultural guide will take you on an informative walk around Tae Rak (Lake Condah) and the surrounding wetlands. The lake is made up of 1,700 hectares of significant wetlands and stony rises right next to the historic lava flows of Budj Bim National Park. The Gunditjmara people have sustained life here for tens of thousands of years, and created what is considered to be one of Australia's earliest and largest aquaculture systems. 

The tour starts with a look at the kooyang (eel) holding tank and an overview of their habitat and lifecycle. Walk along the boardwalk and out onto the jetty over the lake, where your guide will give you an overview of the Gunditjmara creation story and point out the extensive marine and bird-life of the lake.

properties.name: Kooyang Yana - Kooyang Walk Full Day Tour
properties.description: The Kooyang Yana - Kooyang Walk Full Day Tour is a great experience for people of all ages. It is a fun and educational way to learn about the Gunditjmara people and their culture, as well as the unique natural environment of the Budj Bim Cultural Landscape.

properties.name: Aboriginal Harbour Heritage Tour
properties.description:
Join your First Nations guide and admire the beauty and history of Sydney Harbour through the lens of the Gadigal people. 

The Royal Botanic Garden Sydney will immerse you in the rich Aboriginal culture of the Traditional Owners of the Sydney city area and help you see the Garden in a new and exciting way. 

On your one-hour tour, you'll stroll along the stunning Sydney Harbour foreshore while listening to stories of Gadigal lifestyle, traditions, history and connection to country and community.

properties.name: Aboriginal Bush Tucker Tour
properties.description:
Walk with your First Nations guide to learn more about bush foods and how these foods were used traditionally and adapted to the modern plate and palate. 

The Royal Botanic Garden Sydney will immerse you in the rich Aboriginal culture of the Traditional Owners of the Sydney city area, the Gadigal and help you see the Garden in a new and exciting way.

properties.name: Inverloch Visitor Information Centre
properties.description:
Are you after the best advice on what to see, where to stay and what to do on the Bass Coast? Then drop by the Inverloch Visitor Information Centre for expert, local knowledge from our friendly staff and volunteers. Use our free booking service, browse through a wide range of local (and regional information) and book tickets to attractions. While you are at our centre, take a look at our Dinosaurs of Darkness display which show cases some of the dinosaur fossil discoveries of the local area.

## [Things To See & Do](https://www.visitbasscoast.com.au/experiences)

## [Events](https://www.visitbasscoast.com.au/events)

## [Accommodation](https://www.visitbasscoast.com.au/stay)

properties.name: Southcombe Port Fairy Caravan Park
properties.description:
Escape on your own, with friends or round up the whole family and park your caravan or pitch a tent at Southcombe Caravan Park. Ideally located close to both the famous South Beach and surfing spot The Passage, and a short stroll into town, guests of all ages will enjoy their stay with facilities specifically designed to meet the needs of all families.

As well as being positioned right next to one of Port Fairy’s most famous beaches, there are plenty of activities to keep guests entertained, including kite flying at the Park’s reserve, exploring the playground or taking a short walk through the dunes to Pea Soup Beach. There’s also access to a variety of structured walking and cycling paths that are great to explore.

With great weather, stunning beaches and top class restaurants only short walk away a holiday in Port Fairy at Southcombe Caravan Park is a must.

properties.name: Mortlake Caravan Park
properties.description:
Situated at the foot of dormant volcano Mt Shadwell, Mortlake is the centre of the rich agricultural and pastoral Great South Coast region of Victoria.

From fishing to gem fossicking in the volcanic rocks of Mt Shadwell, Mortlake has it all. The thriving rural town on the Hamilton Highway has a variety of eating spots, great sporting facilities including a 50-metre swimming pool, skate park, historic bluestone precinct and a relaxed country atmosphere.

Centrally located and within walking distance to all attractions, Mortlake Caravan Park is a great base for exploring the town.

properties.name: Killarney Beach Caravan Park
properties.description:
Need a break from your busy day-to-day life? If it’s embracing some down time and getting back in touch with nature that you crave, then Killarney Caravan Park is the place for you. Nestled in a natural coastal environment just 2 km off the Princes Highway and just minutes from Port Fairy, Killarney is known for its beautiful swimming beach protected by off shore reefs.

Killarney Beach truly is a hidden gem with Victoria’s best whiting fishing, safe snorkeling and paddling in a natural lagoon, pristine surf beaches, amazing birdlife and endless beach walking. There is a large oval and playground for the kids to run and play, and a boat ramp is nearby for your convenience.

Tower Hill State Game Reserve, an inactive volcano that is home to many varieties of native flora and fauna and with a range of walking tracks, is a short drive to the east. The charming Irish township of Koroit, steeped in local history, is just north of Tower Hill and is also within a short drive. A little further East and you’ll find the larger regional city of Warrnambool.

properties.name: Discovery Parks - Warrnambool
properties.description:
Discovery Parks - Warrnambool is your gateway to Great Ocean Road glory. Just a hop away from the 12 Apostles and Port Fairy, it's adventure central!

Discovery Parks - Warrnambool is an ideal destination for travellers looking to experience the beauty of the Great Ocean Road while enjoying the comforts of a well-equipped holiday park. Whether you're planning a short getaway or an extended stay, the park provides a range of accommodation options, including comfortable cabins and well-maintained camping facilities. 

Guests will appreciate the park’s convenient location, close to the town centre and just a stone’s throw from the beach.

properties.name: Gum Tree Caravan Park
properties.description: Quiet family and pet-friendly park on the outskirts of the beautiful historical township of Port Fairy. We have modern, comfortable, self-contained cabins to suit every budget, as well as lovely grassed caravan and camp sites. Kids and pets welcome, we even have pet friendly cabins and an off-leash area for your pet.

properties.name: Discovery Parks - Geelong
properties.description:
Get ready for a smorgasbord of good times at Discovery Parks – Geelong. Five minutes from the heart of Geelong and a short drive trip from the famous Great Ocean Road.

Discovery Parks - Geelong offers a relaxing retreat with a range of accommodation options, including modern cabins and spacious camping sites. The park is well-positioned for guests to explore both the city of Geelong and the nearby coastal attractions of the Bellarine Peninsula. Whether you're looking for a base to explore the region or a peaceful spot to unwind, this park provides a comfortable and convenient stay.

**Camping Facilities:**
The camping facilities at Discovery Parks - Geelong are designed to cater to various needs. The park features both powered and unpowered sites, suitable for caravans, motorhomes, and tents. 

- The powered sites offer access to electricity and water, making them ideal for those traveling with caravans or motorhomes. 
- The unpowered sites provide a more traditional camping experience, set in well-maintained, grassy areas. 

Each site is generously sized, ensuring ample space and privacy for your setup and relaxation.

**Amenities:**
- Camp kitchen fully equipped with cooking facilities, BBQs, and a communal dining area for meal preparation and socializing.
- Modern and clean bathroom facilities with hot showers and ample space.
- Laundry facilities with washing machines and dryers to keep your clothes fresh.
- Free WiFi available throughout the park to stay connected.

**Family-Friendly Features:**
The park is designed with families in mind, offering a variety of features to keep children entertained. The resort-style swimming pool is perfect for a refreshing swim, and the children’s playground provides a safe space for kids to play. The park’s location allows for easy exploration of local attractions, such as the Geelong Botanic Gardens and the Geelong waterfront, which are great for family outings.

**Nearby Attractions:**
Discovery Parks - Geelong is ideally located to explore the many attractions of the Geelong region and the Bellarine Peninsula. The city of Geelong offers a vibrant cultural scene, with attractions such as the Geelong Gallery and the National Wool Museum. The Geelong Waterfront is a popular spot, featuring a range of cafes, restaurants, and scenic walking paths. Just a short drive away, the Bellarine Peninsula offers beautiful beaches, wineries, and charming coastal towns. The Great Ocean Road, with its stunning coastal views and landmarks like the Twelve Apostles, is also within reach for a scenic day trip.

**Pet Policy:**
Pets are welcome on selected sites, but prior approval is required, and availability may be limited. Be sure to check the pet policy when making your reservation.

**Check-In/Check-Out:**
Guests are welcome to check in from 2:00 PM, with check-out by 10:00 AM on the day of departure.

properties.name: Cann River Rainforest Caravan Park
properties.description:
Cann River Rainforest Caravan Park offers 32 Unpowered sites. Camp grounds are for temporary stopover camping, up to 36 hours only.There is only basic utilities in the amenities block. Cold water only onsite.
No powered sites available

properties.name: Treetops Adventure Yeodene
properties.description:
Experience a natural high in the Australian native forest at Treetops Adventure Yeodene. Soar through messmate trees, ride a pegasus, and conquer high monkey bars.

The double-storey ‘Home Tree’ deck offers a 360º bird’s eye view of this rustic paradise!

Treetops Adventure Yeodene has 2 Junior Courses & 6 Tree Ropes Courses to choose from, each packed with thrilling aerial activities and a few more freefall drops and ziplines than our Belgrave park. You might already know what challenge you’d be up for; or you can ask our experienced team on arrival.

properties.name: Discovery Parks - Bright
properties.description:
When evening arrives light your own personal camp fire and toast marshmellows under the stairs (so close you can almost touch them) and tell your kids stories of what it was like when you were a kid out bush. Five minutes from Bright, Bright Freeburgh Caravan Park can be your base for a whole range of activities close by. Fish for trout at the local trout farm, go horseback trail riding, visit the Wandiligong maze, drive to Mt Hotham, Mt Buffalo and Falls Creek, and the famous township of Beechworth. Visit many local wineries and then back to your "tranquility base".

Unique, natural, tranquil and relaxing are some of the words used by our visitors who just keep coming back. The atmosphere here is unique. Kids on their bikes, having a ball in the large heated pool, playing in the rock pools in the river, table tennis, pool or watching TV in the games room, or organised games on the large sports oval.

One of Victoria's spacious parks, located in a picturesque rural setting with a long frontage to the trout filled Ovens river.

The park offers superb views up the valley to Mt Feathertop and Mt Hotham. Regarded as a top family park, it provides a peaceful haven away from the bustle of city life.

The four star cabins are bright and roomy and are set in large surrounds, the van sites are extra large and are all surrounded by large mature trees which are an absolute picture in Autumn and Spring.

Centrally located to the snowfields of Mt Buffalo, Mt Hotham and Falls Creek.

properties.name: Discovery Parks - Mount Buffalo
properties.description: Discovery Parks – Mount Buffalo (formerly Porepunkah Bridge Holiday Park) offers a spacious, tree-lined environment on the banks of the Ovens River and in the foothills of one of Victoria’s most popular national parks.

properties.name: Around and About Tours
properties.description:
Around and About offers you a truly unique touring experience as we take you exploring throughout the many interesting and exciting places Victoria has to offer. We specialise in small personalised tours throughout Melbourne and Victoria.

Around and About is a small family business which was started in June 2004. We specialise in tours for up to 11 people however we can also cater for larger groups on request. Being a small operator we can offer you a much more personalised service than the larger operators.

Travel about in the comfort of our 12-seater bus. We are able to take you places large tour coaches cannot access. We cater for all groups, from solo travelers, adventurous travelers, elderly travelers, students and families. Child seats are available on request.

Some of our most popular destinations are, Great Ocean Road (we visit more sights than any other operator), Phillip Island, Dandenong Ranges, Yarra Valley, Mornington Peninsula ( we are the only operator to cross over the bay by ferry), Echuca (Includes 1 hour underground mine tour at Bendigo), Grampians, Sovereign Hill and many more

properties.name: Golden Country Motel & Caravan Park
properties.description:
Motel Rooms, Self Contained Cabins & Villas and Powered Ensuite Sites
Come and stay and enjoy the quiet and relaxing atmosphere of the Golden Country Motel and Caravan Park.

properties.name: Discovery Parks - Echuca
properties.description:
The mighty Murray River is right on your doorstep at Discovery Parks - Echuca.

Whether you choose a cabin, caravan or if camping is more your style, you’ll be relaxing in no time in our resort style accommodation.

This charming riverside town is one of Australia's finest heritage icons and home to the largest paddle steamer fleet in the world. Explore the Port of Echuca Discovery Centre and take a river cruise, or rent your own houseboat. Delight in Murray Esplanade’s heritage buildings, housing shops and cafes. 

Sample delicious local produce on either the Echuca-Moama Food and Wine Trail or the Farm Gate Trail - or both!

properties.name: Lake House Restaurant
properties.description: Lake House is a world-class destination for travellers seriously interested in food and wine. Contemporary dishes inspire even the savviest and most well-travelled palates, and the Lake House kitchen philosophy of working from with the best available seasonal produce means that travellers get a real sense of the best Australian produce on the plate

properties.name: PT. Leo Estate - Vine & Dine
properties.description: All your needs will be taken care of and your senses entertained! This experience is a perfect mid-week introduction to PT. Leo Estate offering a unique Ultimate Winery Experiences vineyard tour, lunch in the One Hatted, PT. Leo Restaurant and access to the world-class PT. Leo Estate Sculpture Park.

properties.name: Woodbine Tourist Park
properties.description: Enjoy a restful and friendly stay in a relaxing seaside Tourist Park. We are situated in the centre of town; walking distance from the famous 90 Mile Beach and the Gippsland Lakes on your doorstep. Shops and restaurants are only a hop, skip and a jump. The Bowls Club is across the road with tasty Australian Cuisine.

properties.name: Worn Gundidj Guided Walking Tour
properties.description:
Experience Tower Hill through an indigenous lens with a guided bush & nature tour. Connect with a 65,000 year old culture, discover one of Victoria's oldest dormant volcanoes and get close to some of Australia's most iconic animals.

From geological wonders to Aboriginal settlement, colonial destruction to revegetation, explore the history of Australia's first National Park.

properties.name: Melbourne Museum - Bunjilaka Aboriginal Cultural Centre
properties.description:
Experience the vibrant cultures of Indigenous Australia and see one of the most significant Aboriginal cultural collections in the world. 

Your expert guide will take you through the award-wining First Peoples exhibition, Bunjilaka Aboriginal Cultural Centre and Milarri Gardens and share insight into the rich traditions of performance, and artwork.

With two kilometres of private beach access hugging the Murray River, over 160 acres of bushland and surrounded by over 20,000 acres of state park, Ingenia Holidays Murray Bend is the true definition of a nature escape.

Set in the heart of Marysville with the pristine mountain stream running through the holiday park we have romance, views, family fun, tranquility and everything you need for a great value holiday package at the top of the Yarra Valley.

Just a short trip from Melbourne through the beautiful Yarra Valley vineyards and the great mountain countryside the magnificent sub alpine Marysville village awaits you. Surrounded by beautiful mountain ranges, amazing bushwalks, driving tracks and an endless list of attractions and things to do, it is the perfect spot for a stay in one of our luxury romantic cabins by the river, great value family cabins close to all the amenities.

properties.name: Lake Colac Holiday Park
properties.description:
Relax and unwind at Lake Colac Holiday Park, located in the heart of Victoria's stunning Otway region. This peaceful park is the perfect base for exploring the natural beauty of the area, including the world-famous Great Ocean Road, nearby wineries, and national parks. 

Family-friendly facilities make Lake Colac Holiday Park a great choice for travellers with kids. Enjoy a refreshing dip in the swimming pool, let the little ones loose on the playground, and prepare meals together in the camp kitchen. 

Located in Colac, Victoria, Lake Colac Holiday Park is just a short walk from the charming town centre with its shops, cafes, and restaurants.

properties.name: Breeze Holiday Parks - Halls Gap
properties.description:
Renowned for heritage-listed Grampians National Park, incredible hikes, wildlife and Indigenous history, Halls Gap is an unspoilt location for the adventurous and the curious.

Breeze Holiday Parks - Halls Gap not only offers exceptional Halls Gap accommodation, it also has a fantastic range of activities and facilities for you to enjoy! We offer a unique combination of a national park setting with the convenience of being in the centre. Right on the doorstep is the small village offering up world-class dining, breweries, wineries, interesting native wildlife and enough to do for a week or two.

Breeze Holiday Parks - Halls Gap is located right at the base of the Grampians Mountain range, the tranquillity allows you to relax and enjoy your leisure time.

The Princetown Recreation Reserve is located six kilometres east of the 12 Apostles, adjacent the Gellibrand River.

Offering powered and unpowered sites at very affordable prices, bookings are essential. Cash only no eftpos facilities available.

Stay a while and discover Ararats historical and cultural past, with the art galleries and museums. Tour the infamous lunatic asylum J Ward and available during the day or take a ghost tour at night. Stroll in Alexandrias Gardens, through the shops and experience the dining options. Ararat is an ideal base to explore the regional attractions which include wineries, the Pyrenees Ranges and the Grampians National Park.

Searoad Ferries is the iconic car and passenger ferry service sailing Melbourne’s Port Phillip Bay between Sorrento and Queenscliff.

The circuit starts at the Eildon Lions day visitor area car park, but you can join the trail from any pondage visitor area along the waterfront.

Begin by walking along Riverside Drive and following the path to the end of the road. Cross the Eildon Pondage Power Station over the Goulburn River and follow the Futurefish Eildon Fishing trail past benches and fishing spots. Along the way, you'll find plenty of Instagram-worthy spots, including two picturesque jetties and a view of the Eildon Dam Wall from the Goulburn Valley Highway Bridge.

Breamlea is a unique coastal village on the south coast of Victoria, mid-way between Barwon Heads and Torquay. Less than 100 kilometres from Melbourne and 20  kilometres from Geelong it features the nearest surf beach to both cities.

Take a two minute stroll along the designated tracks through the dunes and you’ll discover the glorious Bancoora Ocean Beach. The Bancoora Surf Life Saving Club patrols the beach every weekend from summer to early autumn.

Tucked away amongst the gums and tea-tree, Breamlea Caravan Park offers a cosy, relaxed holiday experience. The Park has a range of powered camping and caravan sites plus comfortable one and two bedroom Eco Villas. 

The Park layout means you’re never far from one of the two amenity blocks, recreation room with table tennis and air hockey or BBQ shelter. The park office incorporates a well stocked general store and cafe.

Breamlea Caravan Park is a great place for kids, offering a children’s playground, basketball area and direct access to the beach.

The curling waves are a favourite with board riders and bodysurfers, while anglers can try their luck at the beach or along nearby Thompsons Creek. There are also plenty of walks along designated dune tracks and the wetlands.

Spacious toilet, shower room, Laundry facilities $4 for washing and $2 for drying ($1 coins). 

Clothes lines provided.  Variety of shaded and sunny sites, powered and non powered, water also available. 

2 tracks to Stingray Bay, about 300m. Small store at site open M-F 9-2. Managed by Barwon Heads Council. 

Lovely quiet Beautiful clean beach. Lifesavers on weekend at beach to East of Stingray Beach.

properties.description: Bushman's Rest Caravan Park is located in a beautiful, tranquil, shady setting on the foreshore of Lake Cullulleraine.

properties.name: Bright Freeburgh Caravan Park
properties.description: Bright Freeburgh Caravan Park is set directly on the banks of the Ovens river in the valley of mountains.

properties.name: Breamlea Caravan Park
properties.description: Breamlea Caravan Park is the home to the nearest surf beach to Melbourne

properties.name: Bonnie Doon Caravan Park
properties.description: Bonnie Doon Caravan Park is a small town situated in Northeast Victoria on Lake Eildon close to the High Country.

properties.name: Beechworth Holiday Park
properties.description: Come and relax in Beechworth Holiday Park's beautiful bush environment at the junction of Silver and Spring Creeks.

properties.name: Ardern's Caravan Park
properties.description: Ardern's Caravan Park Myrtleford is a friendly family park

properties.name: Anglesea Family Caravan Park
properties.description:
The Anglesea Family Caravan Park is the perfect holiday destination to explore and create memories. 

Just off the Great Ocean Road and alongside the picturesque Anglesea River and Surf Beach, it’s a must for your next adventure in nature, a weekend away or overnight camp.

properties.name: Pyramid Hill Caravan Park
properties.description: Pyramid Hill Caravan Park is centrally located, next to the local swimming pool, and within walking distance to the town centre. Aside from powered and unpowered camping sites, an ensuite cabin is also available. The campground includes basic amenities, a dump point and laundry facilities.  Call to enquire about current rates and for bookings.

properties.name: Bridgewater Caravan Park
properties.description: Bridgewater Caravan Park is a family-friendly campground located on the banks of the Loddon River. Facilities and amenities include a camp kitchen, swimming pool, playground, barbeques, amenities blocks with laundry, and a boat ramp. Call for enquiries and bookings.

properties.name: Swifts Creek Caravan & Tourist Park
properties.description: Swifts Creek Caravan & Tourist Park provides powered and unpowered sites suitable for tents and caravans.  Facilities include playground, laundry area, BBQ and showers. Bookings and payments are made through IGA Swifts Creek.

properties.name: Smiths Mill Campground
properties.description: Smiths Mill Campground

properties.name: Sun Siesta Caravan Park
properties.description: Located on Sturt highway, Sun Siesta Village Caravan Park offers cabins and access for caravans. It is also suitable for tents and large rigs. Facilities include toilets, showers,BBQ, picnic tables, phone, drinking water and laundromat.

properties.name: Clear Water By the Murray Caravan & Tourist Park
properties.description: Clearwater Caravan Park is opposite the Marray River in Tintaldra. It offers self contained cabins for up to 5 people, including en-suite, small kitchen, TV, air conditioner and linen.  They offer powered and unpowered sites.  Cannoe hire is also available, along with a games room to keep the kids entertained.
properties.fees: AUD $30 night powered sites/ AUD $77 Self-contained cabin/AUD $20-25 unpowered sites

properties.name: Wood Wood Caravan Park
properties.description:
Steve and Rosie would like to welcome you to come and stay with them at Wood Wood Caravan Park. 

The recently purchased  business have re-opened the general store / café that fronts onto the park, performing extensive renovations in the process.

properties.name: Avoca Caravan Park
properties.description: Avoca Caravan Park is situated the township of Avoca in the Pyrenees Region of Central Victoria. The Caravan Park is ideally suited to the overnight traveller or holiday maker looking for a place to base themselves whilst of enjoying the region and day trips to other areas. The park offers a unique Australian bush setting with the Avoca Golf Course surrounding the park offering a chance to play golf or just enjoying a nice leisurely stroll.

properties.name: Bunjil's Lookout
properties.description: Deposit box campsite, 30 mins from Geelong, beautiful location and great facilities.

properties.name: Shoreline Drive Campgrounds
properties.description:
Access:
The western section of the park is accessible by a sealed road via Seaspray and Golden Beach. Located along Shoreline Drive, the campground has ready access to the beach and is in a coastal camping setting.

Bookings:
No bookings, no fees. Camping is on a first in, first-served basis. Dogs are allowed only at sites 1 -6.

Campsites:
There are 19 campgrounds available, consisting of 65 campsites suitable for tents only; 50 campsites suitable for both tent or caravan; and 6 campsites suitable for campervans. Each campsite can accommodate up to six people and one vehicle. All campsites are unpowered.

Facilities:
Non-flush toilets are available at campground 3, 5, 8 and 9

properties.name: Lakes Entrance Recreation Reserve & Camping Ground
properties.description:
The Lakes Entrance Recreation and Camping Reserve is one of Victoria’s 175 Crown Land Caravan Parks established to provide affordable holidays for all Victorians. The Reserve is managed by a Committee of Management appointed by the responsible Minister under the Crown Land (Reserves) Act 1978.                                                                    A beautiful waterfront park, located on the sheltered North Arm. The reserve has spacious powered and un-powered sites with ample provision for large Motorhomes and RV’s.

Adjacent to the Bowls Club and just a 3 minute flat walk to the main shopping centre, restaurants, and attractions. The only park located on the water’s edge, the park is popular for fishing, boating and kayaking.

The park is pet friendly. Pets are allowed on leads all year round. The park is perfect for families, overnight stays and travellers of all ages. The park also provides boat and trailer parking.

properties.name: Gibston Steps walk
properties.description: Time and the elements have meticulously carved and refined the steps into a magnificent natural marvel, complemented by the presence of two prominent rock formations, Gog and Magog, which gracefully protrude from the nearby ocean. These formations are readily visible from the observation platform situated atop the steps.

properties.name: Sawpit Picnic Area - Mt Clay State Forest
properties.description: This is a large and level bush camping area located in a state forest, where a sawmill used to stand. There are good amenities and plenty of shade, with Whalers Point only a short walk away. To access, drive 3km further from the main road. The road is sealed-turned-gravel (last 500m) and the site is accessible by all vehicles.

properties.name: River Road Reserve
properties.description: This bush camping area is located on the bank of the Ovens River, just by the bridge, and it is accessible via a short dirt road. There are no amenities and space is limited. The site is quite shaded and when the water level is low, there is a small sandy beach. Great for swimming and fishing.

properties.name: Hamiltons Crossing Rest Area
properties.description: Lovely riverside campground with no facilities, but with an abundance of recreational opportunities - fishing, swimming and walking are all great here! Access is through a gate marked on the GPS and via a 50m dirt track until you reach the river.

properties.name: Golden Beach RV Rest Stop
properties.description: This spacious rest area with fantastic amenities is located in the centre of town and close to the beach. It offers scenic views and many walking tracks. There are a few local shops and a petrol station nearby. Maximum stay is 48hrs. Only for self-contained vehicles.

properties.name: Deep Lake Recreation Reserve
properties.description: Deep Lake Recreation Reserve offers unpowered sites, many set right on the edge of the water. There are 7 available for pre-booking to avoid disapointment. Sites are suitable for tents and caravans. Camp fires are permitted in delegated areas. Facilities include covere BBQ shelter, ammenities block, drinking water, public shelter, a floating jetty and wood heaters. There are also club rooms for hire.  Payments can be made at the local cafe in town, or a phone booking can be made.
properties.fees:
AUD $10 per adult per night $35 per week
Under 18's are free

properties.name: Hammond Road Campground
properties.description:
Hammonds Campground is located 12km inland from Aireys Inlet in a natural bush setting. Relax at camp and enjoy the company of kangaroos and other native wildlife or explore one of the many walking and bike riding trails in the area.

Set among dry forest and woodland, Hammonds Campground is an ideal location for wildlife viewing and relaxation. Kangaroos and native birds frequent the area, and if you’re lucky you may even see a koala. Nearby Distillery Creek Day Visitor Area has a range of walks and shared trails for those looking for recreational activities.

The campground offers 16 campsites, each accommodating up to six people. Sites 1-4 provide direct vehicle access and are suitable for camper trailers and caravans. Sites 5-16 are suitable for tents only with a parking area situated close by. All campsites are unpowered. Campground facilities include non-flush toilets, shared fireplaces and shared low tables/seats. Remember to bring your own firewood to protect the surrounding wildlife habitat. Advanced bookings and payment are required year-round.

properties.name: Leanganook Picnic Area Mount Alexander Regional Park
properties.description: Around 7km from Faraday, access by Farraday Sutton Grange road then Joseph Young Dr. The camp entry will be on the left. On the hilltop of the Mount Alexander Park, there are many trees with picnic tables areas and camp fires. A building is in the middle of this place with flushing toilets. Walking tracks start from here.

properties.name: Merbein Common Camping No.2
properties.description: Dirt campsite on banks of the Murray River.

properties.name: Piangil Park Area
properties.description: Large grassy area available for overnight parking. Toilets and showers available (showers in the rear building). Support the town by buying local.

properties.name: Omeo RV Stop
properties.description: RV parking area at Livingstone Park in town. Toilets, picnic tables and bins available, some shade from trees. Located on Creek St on the W side of town. Park behind the RV signage. Max stay: 36hrs.

properties.name: White Womans Waterhole Won Wron State Forest
properties.description: This beautiful and calm campground has lots of level sites between the trees. Accessible for long vehicles. At the end of the area there is a toilet (privy), it is very clean but has no water. No rubbish bins or other facilities available. There are several picnic tables and fireplaces in the picnic area. This is a great place to start several walks that are described on signs. No signal.

properties.name: Picnic Gully Mt Alexander Regional Park
properties.description: Small vehicles only. Big area in the heart of the Oak forest, high trees. Some picnic tables and campfires. No rubbish bins, take your garbage with you!

properties.name: Mt Sturgeon Rest Area
properties.description: Basic rest area on Glenelg Hwy. Picnic tables and some shade from trees available. 2km W of Dunkeld or 30km NE of Hamilton.

properties.name: Brooks River Reserve
properties.description: Large free camp area next to Goulburn River. Toilets available and it's a nice spot for fishing. Located on Brooks Cutting Rd, 4km W of Alexandra via Swann Rd. Signposted.

properties.name: Heyfield RV Rest Stop
properties.description: Free camping area at the Middle Sportsground oval in Heyfield. Camping is in S area, shady and sunny spots available. Toilets and dump point available, please take your rubbish with you. Donation requested. Entrance is on McFarlane St, signposted. Max stay: 48hrs.

properties.name: Mount Franklin Reserve Campground Hepburn Regional Park
properties.description: Short drive (sealed) off main road, SC and non-SC. Toilets, picnic tables, fireplaces, non-drinkable tap water and walking track to lookout.

properties.name: Girgarre Town Park
properties.description: Free camp area on Morgan Cres in the centre of Girgarre. Toilets, hot showers, piicnic tables, BBQ and a dump point available. Also a playground for the kids! Key for showers available at post office. No camping on second Sunday of the month due to market. Max stay:4 days.

properties.name: Plantation Campground North Grampians
properties.description: Plantation Campground, located just outside Grampians National Park, provides 30 campsites surrounded by pine forest. Sites are suitable for vehicle based camping, camping trailers and caravans. Facilities include bush showers, picnic tables, and wood fireplace. You will need to provide your own water and wood for campfires.  Advanced bookings are not required.
