properties.name: Beaufort Lake Caravan Park
properties.description: On the shores of beautiful Beaufort Lake, Beaufort Lake Caravan Park is picturesque and peaceful - wake to the sunrise over the lake. The park has 54 tourist sites. These consist of 18 powered sites, 12 unpowered sites, 19 powered ensuites, three budget ensuite cabins and three deluxe waterfront cabins.

properties.name: Macarthur Recreation Reserve
properties.description: This is a large and grassy campground located close to town and Eumeralla River. It offers good amenities, incl. powered sites at AUD10 per night. Maximum stay of 72hrs applies.

properties.name: Oxley Recreation Reserve
properties.description:
Oxley Recreation Reserve features clubrooms with kitchens, toilets, and hot showers. 

Recreational activities include tennis courts, a playground and access to King River.

properties.name: Rainbow Caravan Park
properties.description: Rainbow Caravan Park is situated in a peaceful setting close to town. Powered and unpowered sites are available as well as a free BBQ. Phone for rates and bookings.

properties.name: Akoonah Park
properties.description: Akoonah Park offers showground camping with toilet and shower facilities. Bookings are required. Maximum stay of 21 days.

properties.name: Wycheproof Caravan Park
properties.description:
This is a community run caravan park with powered and unpowered sites. The lovely trees and grassed park provide a clean and well maintained ablution block, plus a recently extended camp kitchen.

The Park is close to all amenities in the Wycheproof Township. Check out the new wetland area being developed nearby – they are within walking distance to the famous smallest known as Mountain “Mt Wycheproof”. Walk or drive or ride to the summit and enjoy the amazing changing views.

Watch out for the grain trains travelling through the centre of town.

Enjoy the amazing eateries and talk to the friendly folk. Come for a night and stay a bit longer.

properties.name: Lake Bolac East Beach Visitor Area
properties.description: East Beach Reserve camping area is located along Lake Bolac and is suitable for caravans and motorhomes. Facilities include fire pits, and picnic tables. Camping fees are collected by park ranger.

properties.name: Stapylton Campground
properties.description: Stapylton Campground is one of the best places to stay when exploring the Northern Grampians. It is close to a great selection of day walks, Aboriginal rock shelters, world-class rock climbing, picnic areas and day visitor sites.

properties.name: Eskdale Caravan Park
properties.description: Situated on the banks of the Little Snowy Creek, Eskdale Caravan Park consists of powered and unpowered sites. Facilities include amenities block, laundryBBQ, and camp kitchen. Pets are permitted. Fuel and kiosk are available.

properties.name: Lake Watchem
properties.description: Lake Watchem camping area provides powered and unpowered sites for tents, caravans and motorhomes. Facilities include toilets, water, showers, wood fireplace and sheltered area with picnic tables. Pets are not allowed.

properties.name: Quambatook Caravan Park
properties.description: Quambatook Caravan Park consits of powered and unpowered sites for tents, caravans and motorhomes. Facilities include toilets, showers, laundry area and picnic tables. Pets are allowed.  Bookings can be made by phone.

properties.name: Nyah Village Caravan Park
properties.description:
Nyah Village Caravan Park offers powered and unpowered sites, suitable for caravans, tents and large RV's. 

There are also cabins available for hire. Facilities include campers kitchen, laundry area, BBQ, hot showers and kiok. There is a manager on-site.

properties.name: Murrayville Caravan Park
properties.description: Murrayville Caravan Park provides 8 powered sites and several unpowered sites. Facilities include showers, toilets, ablution block, BBQ and water supply. Pets are permitted.

properties.name: Penshurst Caravan Park
properties.description: Penshurst Caravan Park provides powered and unpowered sites. Facilities include showers, BBQ, playground, laundry area, public swimming pool (located next door), and tennis courts. Pets are allowed. Bookings made at the Penshurst Post Office.

properties.name: Nangiloc Caravan Park
properties.description: Nangiloc Caravan Park offers powered and unpowerd sites suitable for tents, caravans and motorhomes. Facilities include BBQ area and swimming pool. Bookings can be made via phone.

properties.name: Troopers Creek Campground
properties.description: Troopers Creek Campground is located in North Grampians National Park. The camping area is suitable for vehicle based camping, camper trailers and caravans. Facilities include toilets, fireplace and picnic tables. Local attractions include Mt Difficult and Tilwinda Falls.  Camping permits are required.

properties.name: Murrabit Recreation Reserve
properties.description: Murrabit Recreation Reserve offers powered and unpowered sites suiteable for tents and caravans. Camping fees are collected by the caretaker.

properties.name: Country Gardens Caravan Park
properties.description: Country Gardens Caravan Park offers 41 sites situated in a rual setting. A range of accomodation is available including ensuite cabins, powered and unpowered campsites. Facilities include toilets, showers, BBQ area, laundry and kiosk. Pets are allowed.

properties.name: Warracknabeal Caravan Park
properties.description: Situated on the banks of Yarriambiack Cree, Warracknabeal Caravan Park offers powered and unpowered sites suitable for caravans or camping. Facilities include BBQ, drinking water, camp kitchen, toilets, hot showers and washing machines.

properties.name: Willow Park
properties.description: Located alongside Latrobe River, Willow Park campground offers free, non powered sites. Faclities include toilets, water, and BBQ. Mobile reception, internet access and TV reception are also available. In the area you can enjoy bush walks and fishing. This is a 24 hour stop over.

properties.name: Bills Astro Garden
properties.description:
Bills Astro Garden offers free camping with a wealth of astronomy insights from the owner, Bill. 

The site is pet-friendly and accessible to self-contained vehicles like motorhomes and caravans, with a maximum stay of 48 hours.

properties.name: Daylesford Holiday Park
properties.description: A spacious tranquil park surrounded by trees and only a short walk from the beautiful town of Daylesford – the spa capital of Australia.

properties.name: Buckety Plain Campground
properties.description: Free camp area in Alpine National Park. Toilets and picnic tables and plenty of shade available. Steep, winding road to get here. Signposted. Located 4km SE of Nelse via Bogong High Plains Rd.

properties.name: Raspberry Hill Campground
properties.description: Grassy rest area in Alpine National Park. Picnic tables available. Located on Bogong High Plains Road, 19km W of Omeo Hwy.

properties.name: Providence Ponds Rest Area
properties.description: Basic parking area at Highway A1. Toilets, picnic tables and rubbish bins available. Good area for rest or an overnight stay if you are tired. Road noise.
